\implies\ln(1+x)-\ln(1-x)=?
\left(-\frac1{\sqrt3i}\right)^{2n+1}=-\left(\frac1{\sqrt3i}\right)^{2n+1}=-\frac1{\sqrt3i}\frac1{(\sqrt3i)^{2n}}=-\frac1{\sqrt3i}\frac1{3^n(-1)^n}=\frac i{\sqrt3}\frac{(-1)^n}{3^n}
\frac i{\sqrt3}\ln\frac{1-\frac1{\sqrt3i}}{1+\frac1{\sqrt3i}}=\frac i{\sqrt3}\ln\frac{\sqrt3+i}{\sqrt3-i}=\frac i{\sqrt3}\ln\left(\frac{\sqrt3}2+i\frac12\right)
=\frac i{\sqrt3}\ln e^{(2n\pi i+ i\frac\pi3)}=\frac{i(2n\pi i+ i\frac\pi3)}{\sqrt3}=\frac{-2n\pi-\frac\pi3}{\sqrt3}
n=0
